      <p></p>
<p>These messages emphasize practical and emotional support offered to the bereaved family and friends.  These can be used in conjunction with offering specific help, like bringing meals or running errands.</p>
<li>I am so sorry for your loss.  Please let me know if there's anything I can do.</li>
<li>Sending you strength and love as you grieve the loss of your mother.</li>
<li>Please accept my heartfelt sympathy. I am here for you if you need anything at all.</li>
<li>My thoughts and prayers are with you and your family.  Don't hesitate to reach out.</li>
<li>I'm deeply saddened by your loss. Please know you're not alone in this.</li>
<li>In this time of sorrow, may you find comfort in the love surrounding you.</li>
<li>I'm here to help in any way possible, please don't hesitate to ask.</li>
<li>Please know that you are in my thoughts and prayers.</li>
<li> I am deeply sorry for your loss and sending my love and support.</li>
